      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a good summary. i've also been reading some critiques that say originalism is just a way to justify certain political outcomes or that it's outdated for modern times. how do scholars usually respond to those criticisms? like, what's the counter-argument to the idea that it's just being used for political ends?",
